'''Effasu''' (or '''Effasu-Mangyea''') is a farming community in the [[Jomoro District]] in the [[Western Region (Ghana)|Western Region]] of [[Ghana]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/312777/1/gas-taskforce-inspects-osagyefo-badge-at-efasu.html | title=Gas Taskforce inspects Osagyefo Badge at Efasu | publisher=modernghana.com | accessdate=September 8, 2012}}</ref> about 150&nbsp;km west of [[Takoradi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ghanaoilwatch.org/index.php/ghana-oil-and-gas-news/272-ghana-gas-steers-off-litigation |title=Ghana Gas Steers Off Litigation As Technical Studies Sway Project Site to Atuabo |date= 11 February 2012 |author=J. Ato Kobbie |work=Ghana Oil Watch}}</ref> The [[Osagyefo Barge]] is located at Effasu.

