{{Infobox newspaper | name = elplural.com | motto = Progressive Daily Newspaper | Logo = | image = Plural logo.jpg | pie = | type = Digital daily | headquarters = Gran Vía, 64 [[Madrid]] [[Spain]] | foundation = {{start date and age|2005|09|19}} | founder = Enric Sopena<ref name="EsD2017"/> | political = Aligned with [[Spanish Socialist Workers' Party]] | language = Spanish | publisher= Corporate Communicator | editor asociado = | ISSN = | website = https://www.elplural.com | chiefeditor =Marcos Paradinas}}
'''elplural.com''' is a [[spanish language]] [[news site]] which has been publishing since 19 September 2005. It defines itself as a combination of information with opinion which tries to offer its readers general interest news.<ref name="birth">{{cite web |archivedate=3 February 2014 |language=spanish |trans-title=A new digital newspaper is born, Elplural.com, directed by the journalist Enric Sopena |url=http://www.elperiodicoextremadura.com/noticias/sociedad/nace-un-nuevo-diario-digital-elplural-com-dirigido-por-periodista-enric-sopena_194699.html |date=19 September 2005 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203092629/http://www.elperiodicoextremadura.com/noticias/sociedad/nace-un-nuevo-diario-digital-elplural-com-dirigido-por-periodista-enric-sopena_194699.html |title=Nace un nuevo diario digital, Elplural.com, dirigido por el periodista Enric Sopena |website=elperiodicoextremadura.com |accessdate=3 September 2018}}</ref>
== History == elplural.com was born as a project by the Catalan journalist Enric Sopena,<ref name="birth"/><ref name="EsD2017"/> whose previous experience came from audiovisual or written media such as ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' and [[Televisión Española|TVE]]. Despite its geographical origin in Catalonia, ''El Plural'' deals with national and international topics, and over time a fixed section has focused on [[Andalusia]], together with other regional sections. From 2010, Enric Sopena became a shareholder of the newspaper's publishing company. Until then the ownership of this medium was in the hands of a company linked to Lavinia TV.<ref name="PD2009"/><ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170420143559/http://www.vanitatis.elconfidencial.com/television/2010-09-03/enric-sopena-se-compra-elplural-com_492619/ |url=http://www.vanitatis.elconfidencial.com/television/2010-09-03/enric-sopena-se-compra-elplural-com_492619/ |title=Enric Sopena se compra elplural.com |language=spanish |trans-title=Enric Sopena buys ElPlural.com |first=Eduardo |last=Verbo |website=[[El Confidencial]] |date=3 September 2010 |accessdate=3 September 2018 |archivedate=20 April 2017 |deadurl=no}}</ref>
On March 22, 2017, the General Shareholders' Meeting of elplural.com accepted the retirement request of Enric Sopena as director of the newspaper, becoming 'President 'Emeritus', writing an opinion column titled 'Cabos Sueltos'.<ref name="2d460bab">{{Cite web |last=Moreno |first=Marisu |title=Angélica Rubio sustituye a Enric Sopena en la dirección de ELPLURAL.COM |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903164853/https://www.elplural.com/comunicacion/angelica-rubio-sustituye-a-enric-sopena-en-la-direccion-de-elplural-com_101159102 |date=22 March 2017 |url=http://www.elplural.com/comunicacion/2017/03/22/angelica-rubio-sustituye-enric-sopena-en-la-direccion-de-elpluralcom |archivedate=3 September 2018 |website=El Plural |language=spanish |trans-title=Angélica Rubio replaces Enric Sopena as manager of elplural.com}}</ref>
The journalist Angélica Rubio became the director of the site, having served as Economics editor.<ref name="2d460bab"/><ref name="EsD2017">{{cite news |url=http://www.esdiario.com/822404508/Sopena-deja-la-direccion-de-El-Plural-en-manos-de-una-habitual-de-La-Sex.html |accessdate=4 September 2018 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324022510/http://www.esdiario.com/822404508/Sopena-deja-la-direccion-de-El-Plural-en-manos-de-una-habitual-de-La-Sex.html |trans-title=Sopena leaves the address of "El Plural" in the hands of a regular from La Sexta |date=23 March 2017 |language=spanish |archivedate=24 March 2017 |work=EsDiario.com |title=Sopena deja la dirección de “El Plural” en manos de una habitual de La Sexta}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://dircomfidencial.com/medios/el-plural-acusa-la-caida-en-el-negocio-y-pierde-100-000-euros-20170822-0403/ |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180904090822/https://dircomfidencial.com/medios/el-plural-acusa-la-caida-en-el-negocio-y-pierde-100-000-euros-20170822-0403/ |accessdate=4 September 2018 |date=22 August 2017 |title=El Plural acusa la caída en el negocio y pierde 100.000 euros |language=spanish |archivedate=4 September 2018 |website=DirComfidencial.com |trans-title=''El Plural'' announces fall in business and loses 100,000 euros}}</ref>
==Structure== The newspaper has sections on Politics, Economic, Communications and Society. In addition, elplural.com has a [[Autonomous communities of Spain|Autonomous communities]]' section, focused on [[Catalonia]], the [[Balearic Islands]] and [[Andalusia]]. The latter, since September 26, 2016, is formed by the integration of the ''Andaluces Diario'' newspaper,<ref>{{Cite web |trans-title=ELPLURAL.COM reinforces its territorial expansion with the 'signing' of Andalucesdiario.es |url=http://www.elplural.com/2016/09/23/elpluralcom-refuerza-su-expansion-territorial-con-el-fichaje-de-andalucesdiarioes |deadurl=no |title=ELPLURAL.COM refuerza su expansión territorial con el ‘fichaje’ de Andalucesdiario.es |accessdate=4 September 2018 |surname=Gil |date=23 September 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180904072907/https://www.elplural.com/autonomias/andalucia/elplural-com-refuerza-su-expansion-territorial-con-el-fichaje-de-andalucesdiario-es_91240102 |language=spanish |website=El Plural |first=Sara |archivedate=4 September 2018}}</ref> led by the journalist Antonio Avendaño, who joined from ''[[Público (Spain)|Público]]''.
The Opinion section is composed of conventional articles and analysis, as well as cartoons from the series "Los Calvitos", by humorist Patricio Rocco, aka Pat.
Apart from the usual sections, the newspaper includes various magazines, such as ''El Telescopio'' - dedicated to Technology and Innovation -, ''La Pimienta de la Vida'' - focused on gastronomy and lifestyle - ''Motor'' - automotive sector associated with the Autofácil publication - and ''Playtime'' - leisure and culture.
== Editorial line == ''El Plural'' defines itself as a progressive daily.<ref name="EsD2017"/> It has had connections with [[Socialists' Party of Catalonia|PSC-PSOE]].<ref name="PD2009">{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091118195120/http://www.periodistadigital.com:80/periodismo/internet/2009/11/16/elplura-sopena-lavinia-psoe.shtml |date=16 November 2009 |first=Higinio |url=http://www.periodistadigital.com/periodismo/internet/2009/11/16/elplura-sopena-lavinia-psoe.shtml |trans-title=Enric Sopena's El Plural is owned by the Lavinia Group |last=Mosteiro |deadurl=no |website=PeriodistaDigital.com |title=El Plural de Enric Sopena es propiedad del Grupo Lavinia |language=spanish |archivedate=18 November 2009 |accessdate=4 September 2009}}</ref> It is aligned social-democratically. In 2011, journalist Carlos Carnicero lost his job at the publication following repeated criticism of [[Prime Minister of Spain|Prime Minister]] [[José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero|Zapatero]]'s [[Spanish Socialist Workers' Party|PSOE]] government.<ref>{{cite web |first=Luis |language=spanish |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110317200258/http://www.periodistadigital.com:80/periodismo/internet/2011/03/16/carnicero-sopena-el-plural-censor-despido-nueva-york-zapatero.shtml |url=http://www.periodistadigital.com:80/periodismo/internet/2011/03/16/carnicero-sopena-el-plural-censor-despido-nueva-york-zapatero.shtml |deadurl=no |last=Balcarce |archivedate=17 March 2011 |title=El 'censor' Enric Sopena fulmina a Carlos Carnicero de El Plural.com |trans-title=The 'censor' Enric Sopena fires Carlos Carnicero of El Plural.com |work=PeriodistaDigital.com |date=16 March 2011}}</ref>
