{{Infobox mountain | name = Färichhorn | photo = Balfrin.jpg | photo_caption = The [[Balfrin]] (centre) and the Färichhorn (right) | elevation_m = 3292 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 248 | prominence_ref = <ref>Retrieved from the [[Swisstopo]] topographic maps. The key col is the Gässi (3,044 m).</ref> | parent_peak = [[Monte Rosa]] | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | location = [[Valais]], [[Switzerland]] | range = [[Pennine Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|46|9|19.9|N|7|51|32.1|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
The '''Färichhorn''' is a [[mountain]] of the [[Pennine Alps]], located between the [[Mattertal]] and the [[Saastal]] in the canton of [[Valais]]. It lies north of the [[Balfrin]], at a height of 3,292 metres above sea level.
