{{Expert-subject|Serbia|date=February 2009}} {{Royal house| | surname = Lazarević | type = <!-- Royal house, noble house, etc. --> | native_name = Лазаревић | native_name_lang = sr | other_name = | estate = of Serbia | coat of arms = [[File:Coat of arms of Moravian Serbia.svg|150px|Coat of Arms]] | country = [[Serbia]] | parent house = [[Nemanjić dynasty]] | titles = [[Prince]], [[Despot (court title)|Despot]] | founder = [[Lazar Hrebeljanović]] | final ruler = [[Stefan Lazarević]] | current head = | founding year = 1371 | dissolution = 1427 | ethnicity = [[Serbs|Serbian]] | cadet branches = }}
The '''Lazarević''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Лазаревић}}, {{small|[[plural|pl.]]}} Lazarevići / Лазаревићи, {{IPA-sh|lazǎːrɛv̞itɕ|pron}}) was a [[Serbs|Serbian]] medieval [[royal family]], which ruled [[Moravian Serbia]] and the [[Serbian Despotate]].
The dynasty began with [[Lazar Hrebeljanović]], son of [[Pribac Hrebeljanović]]-a noble at the court of [[Dušan the Mighty]]. Lazar married [[Princess Milica|Milica]], supposedly a member of the reigning [[Nemanjić dynasty]], and was later given the title "Knez" by [[List of Serbian monarchs|Serbian Emperor]] [[Uroš the Weak]]. He gained lands in Central Serbia and through his ties with the Nemanjićs he became the regent of [[Moravian Serbia]]. In the [[Battle of Kosovo]] against the [[Ottoman Empire]], Lazar was killed and Serbia became a vassal state, leading to the end of Serbian sovereignty.
==Monarchs== Rulers of [[Moravian Serbia]] from 1371 to 1427. *[[Lazar Hrebeljanović]] (1371–1389) *[[Stefan Lazarević]] (1389–1427)
==Family tree== [[File:Tsar Lazar and his family.jpg|thumb|''Tsar Lazar and his family'', 1860.]] *Pribac **Draginja, married Kefalija (čelnik) Miša **'''Lazar'''; ''Lazarevići'' **Daughter, married [[Altoman Vojinović]]
;Lazarević: Lazar married [[Milica of Nemanja|Milica]] (Милица) in around 1353 and issued at least seven children:
* Mara (died April 12, 1426), married [[Vuk Branković]] in around 1371 * [[Stefan Lazarević]] (around 1377 - July 19, 1427), prince (1389–1402) and [[Despotes|despot]] (1402–1427) <!-- rest should be moved on Stefan's page, married in [[1405]] Jelena, daughter of [[Francesco II of Lesbos]] (1384-1404). --> * Vuk, prince, executed on July 6, 1410 * Mara or Dragana (died before July 1395), married [[Bulgaria]]n [[tsar]] [[Ivan Shishman of Bulgaria|Ivan Shishman]] in around 1386 * Teodora (died before 1405), married [[Nicholas II Garay|Nikola II Gorjanski]] (who died in 1433), son of [[Nicholas I Garay|Nikola I Gorjanski]], [[ban (title)|ban]] of [[Mačva]] since 1387, ban of [[Croatia]] since 1394, and [[Palatine (Kingdom of Hungary)|Hungarian Palatin]] since 1401 * Jelena or Jela, died March 1443, married [[Đurađ II|Đurađ Stracimirović]], then [[Sandalj Hranić]]<ref>Mrđenović (1987), p.108</ref> * [[Olivera Despina]] (1372 - after 1444), married Ottoman [[Sultan]] [[Bayezid I]] in 1390
