'''Light and Life''' is a [[Gypsy]]-led [[evangelical]] Christian movement, that claims "up to 40% of British Gypsies" are part of it.<ref name="bbc" /> Practitioners [[teetotalism|abstain from alcohol]] and fortune-telling and engage in [[Charismatic Christianity|Charismatic]] prayer.

Its founders include Jackie Boyd, a [[Romani people|Romani]] gypsy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/10/30/gypsy-church-light-and-life-jackie-boyd_n_6075434.html|title=The Born-Again Christian Gypsies Who Are Leading A Cultural Revolution|first=Louise |last= Ridley |date=19 November 2014|publisher=[[The Huffington Post]]}}</ref> The boxer [[Tyson Fury]] is reportedly a member.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/dec/13/tyson-fury-traveller-faith|title=How Tyson Fury’s words shine a light on Traveller faith|first=Sarah|last=Hughes|date=12 December 2015|publisher=|via=The Guardian}}</ref>

As of December 2015, Light and Life has 33 churches and 20,000 followers.<ref name="auto"/>

