{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Territorial Prelature |name = Marawi |latin = Praelatura Territorialis Maraviensis |local = Prelatura Teritoryal ng Marawi |country = [[Philippines]] |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Ozamiz|Ozamiz]] |province = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Ozamiz|Ozamiz]] |denomination = [[Roman Catholic]] |sui_iuris_church = [[Latin Church]] |rite = [[Roman Rite]] |cathedral = [[Cathedral of Maria Auxiliadora]] in [[Marawi]] |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 4,587 |population = 1,184,099 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 13,127 |catholics_percent= 0.8 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Edwin de la Peña]] |bishop_title = [[Prelate]] |metro_archbishop = [[Jesus Dosado]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= |vicar_general = Nilo Tabania }}
The '''Territorial Prelature of Marawi''' ({{lang-la|Praelatura Territorialis Maraviensis}}) is a [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] [[territorial prelature]] under the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Ozamiz|Ozamiz]] in the Philippines.
It comprises parishes in the minority Catholic community of [[Marawi]] and four municipalities in the Lanao Provinces with significant Catholic population: [[Malabang, Lanao del Sur|Malabang]] and [[Balabagan, Lanao del Sur|Balabagan]] in [[Lanao del Sur]], and [[Sultan Naga Dimaporo]] and [[Baloi, Lanao del Norte|Baloi]] in [[Lanao del Norte]]).
==History== * November 20, 1976: Established as the Territorial Prelature of Marawi from the [[Territorial Prelature of Iligan]]
==Leadership== * [[Prelates]] of Marawi (Roman rite) ** Bishop Edwin de la Peña y Angot, M.S.P. (October 22, 2001 – Present) ** Bishop Bienvenido Solon Tudtud (April 25, 1977 – June 26, 1987)
